S'  We prove a structure theorem for multiplicative functions on the Gaussian\nintegers, showing that every bounded multiplicative function on the Gaussian\nintegers can be decomposed into a term which is approximately periodic and\nanother which has a small U^3-Gowers uniformity norm. We apply this to prove\npartition regularity results over the Gaussian integers for certain equations\ninvolving quadratic forms in three variables. For example, we show that for any\nfinite coloring of the Gaussian integers, there exists dfferent nonzero\nelements x and y of the same color such that x^2-y^2=n^2 for some Gaussian\ninteger n, the analog of which over Z remains open.\n'
