S"  The inverse theorem for the Gowers norms, in the form proved by Green, Tao\nand Ziegler, applies to functions on an interval $[M]$. A recent paper of\nCandela and Sisask requires a stronger conclusion when applied to $N$-periodic\nfunctions; specifically, that the corresponding nilsequence should also be\n$N$-periodic in a strong sense.\n  In most cases, this result is implied by work of Szegedy (and Camarena and\nSzegedy) on the inverse theorem. This deduction is given in Candela and\nSisask's paper. Here, we give an alternative proof, which uses only the\nGreen--Tao--Ziegler inverse theorem as a black box. The result is also\nmarginally stronger, removing a technical condition from the statement.\n  The proof centers around a general construction in the category of\nnilsequences and nilmanifolds, which is possibly of some independent interest.\n"
