S'  We consider radial solutions of a general elliptic equation involving a\nweighted $p$-Laplace operator with a subcritical nonlinearity. By a shooting\nmethod we prove the existence of solutions with any prescribed number of nodes.\nThe method is based on a change of variables in the phase plane, a very general\ncomputation of an angular velocity and new estimates for the decay of an energy\nassociated with an asymptotic Hamiltonian problem. Estimating the rate of decay\nfor the energy requires a sub-criticality condition. The method covers the case\nof solutions which are not compactly supported or which have compact support.\nIn the last case, we show that the size of the support increases with the\nnumber of nodes.\n'
